{
  "texts": [
    "Since self-attention layers struggle with modeling the temporal order, SASRec employs positional embedding to retain the temporal information of the sequence.",
    "Thus, for an input interaction sequence S = [𝑣 1, 𝑣 2,..., 𝑣 𝑡], SASRec converts it to vectors using both item embedding table and positional embedding table[v 1 + p 1, v 2 + p 2,..., v 𝑡 + p 𝑡].Subsequently, several self-attention blocks with residual connections are stacked to compute the latent vectors [h 1, h 2,..., h 𝑡].",
    "Finally, the latest latent vector is used to calculate the user's preference scores on each item with the item embedding table:r *,𝑡 +1 = h ⊤ 𝑡 V(3) METHODOLOGYIn this section, we first introduce the details of our proposed framework, FELLAS.",
    "Following this, we propose two inference attacks to evaluate FELLAS's empirical privacy protection capabilities, given that users in FELLAS will upload a noisy version of their data to a third-party LLM server.",
    "Overview of FELLASTo address the poor representation ability of sequential recommendation models in FedSeqRecs due to communication budget limitations and on-device computational resource constraints, our FELLAS employs a pretrained LLM server during the original FedSeqRec training process."
  ]
}